    "title": "Kerala Tourism Capital India is Hiring: Guest Relations Manager (Lead)",
    "description": "If you're a passionate Guest Relations Manager with drive and ambition, Kerala Tourism Capital India in Bengaluru is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout Kerala Tourism Capital India:\nKerala Tourism Capital India is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Plan and execute banquets, events, and MICE functions\n• Coordinate with travel agents and OTAs for occupancy optimization\n• Ensure compliance with FSSAI, health, and safety regulations\n• Handle guest complaints and resolve issues promptly\n• Manage front office operations including check-in/check-out\n• Coordinate housekeeping and maintenance for room readiness\n• Manage reservations and optimize room revenue through yield management\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Any graduate with relevant experience\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Front Office\n• Proficiency in Crisis Management\n• Proficiency in Food Safety\n• Proficiency in OTA Management\n• Proficiency in Opera PMS\n• Proficiency in Yield Management\n• Proficiency in Tour Planning\n• Proficiency in Sommelier Skills\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Learning & development budget\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Flexible working hours\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Bengaluru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Kerala Tourism Capital India!",
